		<div class="comment-body"><p>I should also add that the NUMBER of trades has nothing to do with the VALUE of the exchange.</p>
<p>Two banks moving money back and forth between them equals lots of velocity, and no value exchange (think &#8216;high frequency trading&#8217;.. it creates no value).</p>
<p>A company making a one time purchase of a machine that uses 1/2 of the electricity of the current machine.. huge value creation, with ripple effects (cheaper goods, less resource use, etc.)</p>
