		<div class="comment-body"><p>Quit looking at Mises. He is talking about an agrarian economy in the 19th century. It doesn&#8217;t have the same rules  and those ideas dont work when we have the specialization in the work force that is alot more efficient because you are only doing 1 task, but creates a dependence on everyone else in society because of it.</p>
<p>The Mises economy isn&#8217;t the modern world, in other words.</p>
